trend_summary: 1990s-2020s imagery shows a suburban valley gradually intensifying: new warehouses cluster along the north-western industrial park, residential infill fills vacant lots, and a highway interchange is upgraded. Tree cover is moderately reduced around new buildings, while riparian green corridors remain intact. Overall footprint expands slightly yet remains medium-density suburban.
notable_changes: Large light-roof warehouses added in the north-west industrial zone.
Expansion of commercial/industrial complex beside the central highway junction.
Residential infill on previously treed or vacant lots within the street grid.
Highway/interchange widening and new access roads improving regional connectivity.
Moderate loss of forest edge, but riverside greenbelt largely preserved.
